<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN">
<html>
<head>
<title>Help: Editing page titles and descriptions</title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=iso-8859-1">
<link href="../style.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css">
</head>

<body>
<p class="titlebold">	Editing page titles and descriptions</p>
<p class="text">To edit the page titles and descriptions, open the site you want
  to edit and select Site &gt; Settings and click on the &quot;Page Text&quot; tab.</p>
<p class="text"><strong>Catalog Page</strong> &#8212; This is the page users
  see when they click on &quot;Catalog&quot; in the menu and will display all
  of the items available on an order site.<br>
      <strong>Cart Page</strong> &#8212; This page may be accessed by customers
      after they have added an item to their cart. The can edit their order or
      check out from here.<br>
    <strong>Checkout Page</strong> &#8212; On this page customers choose a
      payment type and fill in billing and shipping information.<br>
    <strong>Pre-invoice Page</strong> &#8212; This page allows customers to review
    their order information before submitting it.<br>
    <strong>Invoice Page</strong> &#8212; The invoice page is displayed after
    an order has been submitted and may be printed by the customer as a receipt.<br>
    <strong>Proof Approval Page</strong> &#8212; For template items that allow
    customers to enter information, a preview is generated which the customer
    must approve by entering their initials before checking out.<br>
    <strong>Login Page</strong> &#8212; Customers may log in or create an account.<br>
    <strong>Account Page</strong> &#8212;<br>
    <strong>Input Page &#8212;</strong> Title and Description <br>
    <strong>Input Options</strong> &#8212; Page Description </p>
</body>
</html>
